    <title>Logging In to Knowledge</title>
    <para><?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T111559-0500" content="You will receive an email w"?><?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T111559-0500"?>W<?oxy_insert_end?>hen
        the administrator creates an account for
        you<?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T111603-0500"?>, you
        will receive an email,
        which<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T111614-0500" content=". The email"?>
        will contain login information (be sure to check your spam folder)<?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T111630-0500"?>.<?oxy_insert_end?>
        <?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T111634-0500"?>This<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T111633-0500" content="which"?>
        will enable
        <?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T111500-0500" content="the "?>you
        to access the Knowledge
        web-application.<?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T111532-0500"?>
        After your first login your password should be changed.<?oxy_insert_end?> If you do not
        receive an email, contact your Knowledge administrator.
        <?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T111529-0500" content="After your first login your password should be changed. "?></para>
    <section>
        <title>User Roles</title>
        <para>Knowledge has
            <?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114235-0500"?>six<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114235-0500" content="6"?>
            roles<?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114231-0500"?>.<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114230-0500" content=" Author, Administrator, and Read"?>.
            Each of these roles have different permissions: <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis>Read role</emphasis>:
                        <?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114518-0500" content="Allows users to"?><?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114518-0500"?>Users
                        with Read role can<?oxy_insert_end?> view content and download content
                        <?oxy_comment_start author="susancastillo" timestamp="20200108T211242-0800" comment="need to confirm this when content release feature is completed"?>releases<?oxy_comment_end?><?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114300-0500" content="."?></para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis>Editor role</emphasis>: Editors modify content, create new
                        content, search, classify, and download content releases</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis>Content Manager</emphasis>: The Content Manager has all the
                        capabilities of the Editor role and can release
                        content<?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114535-0500" content="."?>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis>System Manager</emphasis>: The System Manager has administrative
                        priveleges of the whole environment</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis>Administrator role</emphasis>:
                        <?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114546-0500"?>Administrators
                        c<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114546-0500" content="C"?>an
                        create user accounts, modify user accounts, and
                        ha<?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114603-0500"?>ve<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114603-0500" content="s"?>
                        all the editing
                        function<?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114620-0500"?>ality<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114620-0500" content="s"?>
                        as the Author role with the additional ability to release
                        content<?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114627-0500" content="."?></para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis>Automated</emphasis>: This is a role used for system to system
                        communicaiton<?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200114T114643-0500" content="."?></para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist></para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Login</title>
        <para>To Login you will enter your username and password. If
            you<?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200129T104825-0500" content="&apos;ve"?>
            forg<?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200129T104844-0500"?>e<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200129T104844-0500" content="o"?>t<?oxy_delete author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200129T104827-0500" content="ten"?><?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200129T104830-0500"?>
            either<?oxy_insert_end?> your user name or
            password<?oxy_insert_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200129T104836-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
            select the appropriate link in the Knowledge Login screen. <?oxy_comment_start author="susancastillo" timestamp="20200108T090501-0800" comment="if developers are able to implement logging in with google or MS will need to add content
"?><figure><?oxy_comment_end?>
                <title>Login</title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="images/login-page.png" width="600px"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <textobject>
                        <phrase>Login Page</phrase>
                    </textobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure></para>
        <para>After you succcessfully login to Knowledge you will see the Manager homepage. <figure>
                <title>Homepage of user with Author role</title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="images/knowledge-manager.png" width="600px"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <textobject>
                        <phrase>Manager page of a user with Author role</phrase>
                    </textobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure></para>
        <para>From this page you can: <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>select the <emphasis role="bold">Profile </emphasis> menu option to change
                        your user profile.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis>add</emphasis> a user or <emphasis>modify</emphasis> a user's
                        role if you are an administrator.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>select the <emphasis role="bold">Go To Editor</emphasis> button to be
                        directed to the Knowledge Editor.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>select the <emphasis role="bold">Go To API</emphasis> button to be view
                        the Rest API documentation</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>select the <emphasis role="bold">Logout</emphasis> button to logout of the
                        application</para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist></para>
        <para>
            <figure xreflabel="Admin">
                <title>Homepage of user with Administrator role</title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="images/admin-user-menu.png" width="600px"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <textobject>
                        <phrase>Manager page of a user with Administrator role</phrase>
                    </textobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
        </para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Edit User Profile</title>
        <para>When you select the <emphasis>Profile</emphasis> menu option you are able to modify:
            <?oxy_comment_start author="ColinCavanaugh-Johns" timestamp="20200129T180649-0500" comment="I cannot get this to work, but I would make this a short bulleted list. "?>the<?oxy_comment_end?>
            Display Name, your User Name, your email address and change your password. To save any
            changes made you will need to select the <emphasis>Save</emphasis>button. The
                <emphasis>Cancel</emphasis>button will discard any changes made. <figure>
                <title>User Profile</title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="images/Edit-profile.png" width="600px"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <textobject>
                        <phrase>Edit User Profile</phrase>
                    </textobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure></para>
    </section>
